n to the cluster centre as\nthe NVSS sample. Moreover, we find that their maximum radio luminosity roughly\ncorrelates with cluster mass, although displaying a large scatter. The overall\ngood agreement between NVSS and the mock sample suggests that properties of\nradio relics are indeed governed by merger shock fronts, emitting in a\nhomogeneous fashion. Our study demonstrates that the combination of mock\nobservations and data from upcoming radio surveys will allow to shed light on\nboth the origin of radio relics and the nature of the intracluster medium.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Apr 2017 18:00:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 9 Nov 2017 15:40:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-11-10"}
