 for BMI, and to predict the increase in explained\nheritability with study sample size. Considering the demographic history of\nEuropean populations, in which these GWAS were performed, we further find that\nmost of the associations they identified likely involve mutations that arose\nduring the out of Africa bottleneck at sites with selection coefficients around\n$s=10^{-3}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Apr 2017 20:22:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 7 Dec 2017 18:12:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-03-29"}
